    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-06-30T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-06-30T13:00:00-05:00" n="1008"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1008">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.00/6–3054: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_DCD1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dillon</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-06-30T19:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 30, 1954—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5117. Repeated information Saigon 634, Geneva 449. Department limit distribution.
                    Eyes only <persName corresp="#p_MR2">McClintock</persName> Saigon, <persName
                        corresp="#p_JUA1">Johnson</persName> Geneva. <pb facs="0387" n="1769"
                        xml:id="pg_1769"/>
                    <persName>Jebb</persName> came to see me this morning after his interview with
                        <persName corresp="#p_MFP1">Mendes-France</persName> in the course of which
                    he delivered reply to French <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> of June 26
                        (<gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 4853)<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d1008fn1">Dated June 28, <ref target="#pg_1757">p.
                        1757</ref>.</note> in the form of <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi>,
                    followed by verbal comments along lines outlined in paragraph 2 reference
                    telegram.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName>Jebb</persName> reported that <persName corresp="#p_MFP1"
                        >Mendes</persName> was pleased with text reply and stated that
                        <persName>Parodi</persName> would give us definite French position in day or
                    so. <persName corresp="#p_MFP1">Mendes</persName> also confirmed that
                    negotiations with Viet Minh at Geneva were stalled (Geneva <gloss
                        target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 544, repeated Paris as 519).<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d1008fn2">Telegram <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 544 from
                        Geneva, June 29, reporting a lack of progress in negotiations between the
                        French and the Viet Minh, is not printed. (396.1 GE/6–2954)</note>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_MFP1">Mendes</persName> was somewhat perplexed by
                    reference to “line running generally west from Dong Hoi” as possible partition
                    line for while Dong Hoi is approximately at 17.5 degrees French had been holding
                    out for 18th parallel in face Viet Minh wanting 13th.</p>
                <p>On question of elections, <persName>Jebb</persName> quoted <persName
                        corresp="#p_MFP1">Mendes</persName> as stating that the Viet Minh wanted
                    them to be held in six months but that the French were taking the position that
                    they should be delayed for a year after final settlement and withdrawal of
                    troops had been achieved. This, as presently envisaged, would mean a year and
                    half to two years from now.</p>
                <p>As reported <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 5099,<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d1008fn3">See <ref target="#pg_1757">footnote 3, p.
                        1757</ref>.</note> we delivered reply to <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi>
                    to Foreign Office this morning.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DCD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dillon</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
